tages of the total particles in each class shown beneath. Red arrows show domain movements compared to class 1. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=80375"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="80376">The first five modes of correlated movements. Direction of motion is indicated by the arrows. Informativity of the respective modes measured as variance of the corresponding mode divided by variance of the first mode. Scale bars: 10 nm. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=80376"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="30422"><title>.</title><label>Figure 4</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=30422"/><sd-panel panel_id="80377">Structure of <sd-tag id="sdTag58" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="ryRyR1" ext_ids="P11716" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="RYR1" ext_tax_ids="9986" ext_tax_names="Oryctolagus cuniculus" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">ryRyR1</sd-tag> at a resolution of 17.5 Å. Two views are through the middle slice (top) of the reconstruction and at the level of <sd-tag id="sdTag59" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="assayed" text="sarcoplasmic extentions" ext_ids="GO:0033018" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="sarcoplasmic reticulum lumen" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">sarcoplasmic extentions</sd-tag> 22 Å below (bottom panels). The movement of the outer domains is associated with a visible change in membrane curvature as compared to the apo-structure. This movement is highlighted by red arrows in the right panels. Scale bar: 10 nm. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=80377"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="80378">A <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1725016723sd" category="assay">volume</sd-pretag>-rendered representation of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag26960437sd" parent-tag-id="13">apoRyR1</sd-pretag> (orange) and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag402617855sd"